ADDITIONAL ETHICAL-USE NOTICE (NOT A LICENSE CONDITION)

HEAVEN is an offensive-security tool. The MIT License above governs your
RIGHTS, but the following is the project's STANCE on responsible use:

  HEAVEN must only be used against systems you own or have written
  authorization to test. Unauthorized use of HEAVEN to scan, probe,
  or exploit systems you do not own is illegal in most jurisdictions
  (CFAA in the United States, Computer Misuse Act in the United Kingdom,
  and equivalent laws elsewhere) and is contrary to the intent of this
  project. The `--i-have-authorization` flag is required on every
  scan invocation for exactly this reason.

The MIT License does not require ethical use, but the project's authors
expect it. Reports of misuse will be addressed via the disclosure process
in SECURITY.md.
